page.title: 16Dothill swans
page.content: There have been{swans}on Dothill pools for at least twenty years,ever since the school has been built. The three{pools}are Dothill pool,Tee lake and the School pool.The swans often cross from Dothill pool to Tee lake but they always build their nests and lay their eggs by Dothill pool;they no longer go across to the School pool because it is overgrown with reeds.The swans are popular with the people of Dothill who feed them with bread and other titbits.In the past some swans have been damaged by lead weights and nylon line left behind by careless anglers.This year the cob and pen have reared five cygnets.We hope they will nest here for many years to come.
